.TH ZOOMIX 1 "July 2026" "zoomix 0.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zoomix \- screen zoom, annotation, and image snip utility for Linux Mint X11
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zoomix
.SH DESCRIPTION
Zoomix provides ZoomIt-style zooming, on-screen drawing/text annotation, and image snip capture on Linux Mint Cinnamon X11 sessions.
.SH DEFAULT HOTKEYS
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+1
Toggle zoom mode.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+4
Toggle live zoom mode using Cinnamon's compositor-native magnifier.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+2
Toggle draw mode, including while its text tool is active.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+3
Toggle snip mode.
.SH MODE COMBINATIONS
Switching from Zoom to Draw preserves the magnified view. Switching from that
Draw view to Snip preserves both magnification and annotations in the saved
image, then returns to the Draw view after capture. Starting Snip from idle
captures at 1:1 and closes after capture.
.SH LIVE ZOOM
Applications and the desktop remain interactive while live zoom is active.
Use Ctrl+Shift with the mouse wheel to change magnification. Unmodified clicks,
typing, and scrolling are delivered to the application under the pointer.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/zoomix/config.toml
User configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/Pictures/Zoomix
Default screenshot output directory.
.SH LIMITATIONS
This version targets Linux Mint Cinnamon on X11. Chrome reserves Ctrl+number for tab selection, so Zoomix uses Ctrl+Shift+number by default. Wayland, video capture, timer, DemoType, and OCR behavior are not implemented.
